plainer%3A%20New%2C%20Highly%20Mutated%20Lineage%20Of%20Virus%20That%20Causes%20Covid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organization%20and%20the%20U.S.%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20are%20tracking%20a%20new%2C%20highly%20mutated%20lineage%20of%20the%20virus%20that%20causes%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESix%20cases%20in%20four%20countries%20have%20been%20detected%20since%20late%20July.%20Scientists%20are%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20new%20lineage%2C%20named%20BA.2.86%2C%20because%20it%20has%2036%20mutations%20that%20distinguish%20it%20from%20the%20currently-dominant%20XBB.1.5%20variant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20BA.2.86%20spreads%20faster%20or%20causes%20more%20serious%20illness%20than%20previous%20versions.%20The%20CDC%20said%20its%20advice%20on%20protecting%20yourself%20from%20COVID%20remains%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20new%20about%20COVID%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECOVID%20infections%20and%20hospitalizations%20have%20been%20rising%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20Europe%20and%20Asia%2C%20with%20more%20cases%20in%20recent%20months%20attributed%20to%20the%20EG.5%20%26quot%3BEris%26quot%3B%20subvariant%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20the%20Omicron%20lineage%20that%20originally%20emerged%20in%20November%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20days%2C%20public%20health%20authorities%20have%20documented%20one%20case%20each%20of%20BA.2.86%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20Israel%2C%20and%20three%20cases%20in%20Denmark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20scientists%20say%20about%20BA.2.86%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBA.2.86%20stems%20from%20an%20%26quot%3Bearlier%20branch%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20coronavirus%2C%20so%20it%20differs%20from%20the%20variant%20targeted%20by%20current%20vaccines%2C%20explained%20Dr.%20S.%20Wesley%20Long%2C%20medical%20director%20of%20diagnostic%20microbiology%20at%20Houston%20Methodist%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20whether%20BA.2.86%20will%20be%20able%20to%20out-compete%20other%20strains%20of%20the%20virus%20or%20have%20any%20advantage%20in%20escaping%20immune%20responses%20from%20prior%20infection%20or%20vaccination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20countries%20have%20drastically%20reduced%20testing%20of%20patients%20and%20their%20efforts%20to%20analyze%20the%20genomes%20of%20the%20viruses%20causing%20new%20COVID%20cases.%20In%20that%20situation%2C%20the%20trajectory%20of%20BA.2.86%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20look%20good%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20given%20the%20speed%20at%20which%20new%20cases%20are%20being%20identified%2C%20said%20Dr.%20Eric%20Topol%2C%20a%20genomics%20expert%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Scripps%20Research%20Translational%20Institute%20in%20La%20Jolla%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20many%20mutations%20make%20BA.2.86%20%26quot%3Bradically%20different%20in%20its%20structure%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20earlier%20variants%2C%20Topol%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20question%2C%20he%20added%2C%20is%20whether%20BA.2.86%20will%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20highly%20transmissible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20the%20new%20variants%20make%20people%20sicker%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20emergency%20department%20visits%20and%20hospitalizations%20for%20COVID%20remain%20low%2C%20but%20have%20been%20rising%20since%20early%20July%2C%20according%20to%20data%20on%20the%20CDC%20website.%20So%20far%2C%20however%2C%20doctors%20have%20been%20reporting%20that%20patients%20seen%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20as%20the%20Eris%20variant%20has%20been%20spreading%2C%20are%20not%20as%20sick%20as%20those%20they%20treated%20during%20earlier%20waves%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWider%20spread%20of%20BA.2.86%20would%20likely%20cause%20more%20illness%20and%20death%20in%20vulnerable%20populations%2C%20Topol%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20too%20soon%20to%20know%20whether%20BA.2.86%20will%20cause%20more-severe%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBased%20on%20the%20available%20evidence%2C%20we%20do%20not%20yet%20know%20what%20risks%2C%20if%20any%2C%20(BA.2.86)%20may%20pose%20to%20the%20public's%20health%20beyond%20what%20has%20been%20seen%20with%20other%20currently%20circulating%20lineages%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20CDC%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20vaccines%20protect%20against%20new%20variants%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20waning%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20may%20have%20been%20a%20year%20or%20more%20since%20many%20people%20were%20either%20previously%20infected%20or%20vaccinated%20against%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vaccine%20is%20still%20going%20to%20provide%20you%20great%20defense%20against%20illness%20and%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20Long%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpdated%20COVID%20booster%20shots%20now%20being%20developed%20have%20been%20designed%20to%20target%20the%20Omicron%20subvariant%20XBB.1.5.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModerna%20said%20preliminary%20trial%20data%20suggest%20its%20latest%20version%20of%20the%20vaccine%20shows%20promise%20against%20Eris%20and%20a%20related%20variant%20called%20Fornax%2C%20which%20has%20begun%20to%20circulate%20in%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPfizer%20Inc%20has%20said%20its%20updated%20COVID-19%20shot%20showed%20neutralizing%20activity%20against%20the%20Eris%20subvariant%20in%20a%20study%20conducted%20on%20mice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692449640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fptobkvco_ba286-covid-variant-_625x300_19_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Feris-ba-2-86-who-tracks-new-lineage-of-virus-do-we-need-to-worry-about-covid-again-4311532%22%2C