id%20on%20Saturday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fhow-a-techie-cheated-delhi-businessmen-with-fake-pollution-certificates-4311163%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fhow-a-techie-cheated-delhi-businessmen-with-fake-pollution-certificates-4311163%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fhow-a-techie-cheated-delhi-businessmen-with-fake-pollution-certificates-4311163%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20the%20Rice%20Export%20Ban%20by%20India%20Has%20Achieved%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19161235%2F31764443254_73b92a3ef0_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20on%20July%2020%2C%20to%20ban%20the%20export%20of%20non-basmati%20white%20rice%20has%20disrupted%20global%20rice%20supply%20chains.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInternational%20rice%20prices%20have%20turned%20volatile%20as%20even%20the%20price%20of%20in-transit%20rice%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fagri-business%2Fglobal-rice-market-turns-precarious-as-sellers-hike-prices-of-cargo-in-transit%2Farticle67116229.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecargoes%20has%20increased%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20trade%20contracts%20are%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fforeign-trade%2Findias-rice-export-curbs-puts-contracts-for-2-mln-tons-at-risk-trade%2Farticleshow%2F102018872.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erisk%20of%20getting%20cancelled%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20ban%20would%20deliver%20little%20relief%20to%20Indian%20consumers%20who%20have%20faced%20a%20relentless%20increase%20in%20rice%20prices%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20It%20is%20also%20unlikely%20that%20the%20move%20would%20benefit%20farmers%20by%20way%20of%20higher%20prices%20for%20their%20produce.%20Instead%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20private%20traders%20and%20influential%20lobbies%20like%20those%20representing%20ethanol%20producers%20would%20be%20the%20key%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20export%20ban.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFood%20security%20in%20several%20poor%20rice-importing%20countries%20in%20Africa%20and%20South%20Asia%20is%20at%20risk%20because%20of%20the%20ban.%20Moreover%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20credibility%20as%20a%20reliable%20exporter%20is%20in%20peril.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20with%20or%20without%20the%20ban%2C%20Indian%20farmers%20are%20unlikely%20to%20benefit.%20Rather%2C%20private%20traders%2C%20millers%2C%20and%20exporters%20may%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20transfer%20their%20burden%20of%20losses%20to%20farmers%2C%20expressed%20via%20low%20prices%20they%20would%20pay%20farmers%20in%20the%20forthcoming%20rice%20procurement%20season%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20government%20procurement%20acting%20as%20a%20countervailing%20force%20in%20the%20market.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20that%20the%20ban%20would%20ensure%20foodgrain%20availability%20appears%20unsound%2C%20especially%20because%20it%20has%20done%20so%20little%20to%20actually%20procure%20foodgrains%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20leaving%20the%20field%20open%20for%20private%20trade%20to%20exploit.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20its%20capacity%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20market%20to%20check%20prices%20as%20well%20as%20ensure%20adequate%20availability%20appears%20to%20be%20greatly%20diminished.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20impact%20on%20the%20feed%20industry%20and%20Ethanol%20producers%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBroadly%2C%20the%20categories%20of%20rice%20in%20India%20are%20basmati%2C%20non-basmati%20rice%20(NBR)%2C%20and%20broken%20rice.%20Within%20NBR%20are%20two%20subcategories%20%E2%80%93%20non-basmati%20parboiled%20rice%20(NBPR)%20and%20non-basmati%20white%20rice%20(NBWR).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExports%20of%20broken%20rice%20currently%20account%20for%20about%20one-fifth%20of%20all%20Indian%20rice%20exports%2C%20while%20NBWR%20exports%20account%20for%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20all%20rice%20exports.%20The%20export%20of%20both%20these%20categories%20of%20rice%20has%20now%20been%20banned.%20The%20rest%20is%20basmati%20rice%20and%20NBPR%20which%20constitute%2055%25%20of%20Indian%20rice%20exports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBroken%20rice%20is%20an%20essential%20ingredient%20for%20the%20animal%20feed%20industry%20as%20well%20as%20for%20ethanol%20production.%20In%20September%202022%2C%20the%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1858078%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprohibited%20the%20export%20of%20broken%20rice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Broken%20rice%20prices%20in%20India%20were%20then%20rising%20because%20high%20international%20prices%20were%20influencing%20domestic%20prices.%20In%20response%20to%20rising%20global%20prices%2C%20Indian%20exports%20were%20increasing%20sharply.%20Between%20April%20and%20August%202022%2C%2021.31%20lakh%20metric%20tonnes%20(LMT)%20of%20broken%20rice%20were%20exported%2C%20compared%20to%20just%200.41%20LMT%20in%20the%20same%20period%20of%202018-19%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20more%20than%205000%25%20in%20a%20three-year%20period.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Most%20of%20the%20Indian%20broken%20rice%20went%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fchina-takes-over-as-biggest-importer-of-indian-broken-rice-7968116%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20whose%20imports%20from%20India%20accounted%20for%2097%25%20of%20overall%20Chinese%20rice%20imports%2C%20most%20of%20which%20went%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20feed%20industry%20and%20for%20making%20wines.%20Obviously%2C%20rising%20Indian%20exports%20have%20a%20domestic%20fallout%2C%20implying%20higher%20input%20costs%20for%20the%20Indian%20feed%20industry%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20translated%20into%20higher%20prices%20of%20milk%2C%20eggs%20and%20meat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F03164309%2FDSC2224-1024x684-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F03164309%2FDSC2224-1024x684-1.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F03164309%2FDSC2224-1024x684-1-300x161.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-646849%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22551%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Adithyan%20P.C.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20has%20justified%20the%20ban%20as%20necessary%20to%20ensure%20domestic%20food%20security%20and%20ensuring%20adequate%20availability%20of%20feed.%20However%2C%20two%20weeks%20after%20the%20broken%20rice%20ban%20in%20September%2C%20the%20government%20assured%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1861791%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erice%20availability%20position%20was%20comfortable%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20dismissed%20any%20fears%20of%20an%20availability%20crisis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20also%20justified%20the%20ban%20by%20citing%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20ethanol%20industry.%20Indian%20Ethanol%20production%20has%20been%20increasingly%20relying%20on%20broken%20rice%20and%20maize%20as%20raw%20materials%2C%20especially%20in%20periods%20when%20the%20supply%20of%20sugarcane%20wanes.%20Three%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(FCI)%20started%20supplying%20broken%20rice%20from%20the%20buffer%20stock%20to%20ethanol%20distilleries.%20Since%20then%2C%20supplies%20have%20expanded%20rapidly%3A%20from%200.49%20LMT%20in%202020-21%20to%2010.68%20LMT%20in%202021-22%20and%20to%2013.05%20LMT%20(till%20July%2010)%20with%20five%20months%20remaining%20in%20ongoing%20ethanol%20season.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20total%20production%20of%20broken%20rice%20in%20India%20is%2050-60%20LMT%2C%20of%20which%2032%20LMT%20is%20targeted%20to%20be%20delivered%20to%20ethanol%20distilleries%20this%20year.%20The%20ban%20on%20exports%20thus%20appears%20to%20favour%20domestic%20ethanol%20producers%20by%20ensuring%20adequate%20supplies.%20While%20exporters%20would%20be%20affected%20by%20the%20ban%2C%20rising%20rice%20prices%20in%20India%20provide%20private%20traders%20the%20opportunity%20to%20continue%20making%20higher%20profits%2C%20especially%20if%20state%20procurement%20continues%20to%20sag%20as%20it%20has%20done%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20there%20was%20more%20in%20store%20for%20exporters.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20July%2028%2C%20the%20government%20also%20banned%20the%20export%20of%20de-oiled%20rice%20bran%20(DORB)%2C%20a%20major%20byproduct%20of%20rice%20mills%2C%20till%20November%2030.%C2%A0%20DORB%20is%20extracted%20using%20solvents%20from%20rice%20bran%20that%20has%20an%20oil%20content%20of%2013-19%25.%20With%20a%20rich%20vitamin-B%20composition%2C%20it%20is%20primarily%20used%20in%20animal%20nutrition%20products.%20DORB%20constitutes%2025%25%20proportion%20in%20cattle%20feed%20composition%2C%20thus%20acting%20as%20an%20essential%20ingredient.%20The%20justification%20of%20the%20ban%20on%20DORB%20exports%20is%20based%20on%20the%20claim%20that%20it%20would%20help%20keep%20in%20check%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fmilk-and-rice-prices-remain-high-despite-falling-cpi-inflation-news-296180%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emilk%20prices%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20have%20increased%20because%20of%20higher%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fodder%20prices.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20considered%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fagri-business%2Fban-on-rice-bran-extraction-export-a-retrograde-step-sea%2Farticle67135128.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eretrograde%20step%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20Solvent%20Extractors%E2%80%99%20Association%20(SEA)%20of%20India.%20It%20claims%20that%20it%20would%20affect%20milk%20prices%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Findia-bans-exports-of-de-oiled-rice-bran-after-white-rice-11690562234511.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebarely%201%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20since%20it%20only%20constitutes%2025%25%20of%20the%20feed%20composition.%20Besides%2C%20DORB%20exports%20constitute%20just%2010-12%25%20of%20total%20production%20(6%20LMT%2C%20out%20of%2055%20LMT%20of%20DORB%20output%20was%20exported%20in%202022-23).%20Thus%2C%20the%20ban%20is%20unlikely%20to%20influence%20feed%20prices%20significantly.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20argument%20that%20the%20ban%20would%20help%20dampen%20milk%20prices%20appears%20to%20be%20without%20basis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20July%2024%2C%20in%20the%20same%20week%20when%20NBWR%20and%20DORB%20exports%20were%20banned%2C%20the%20government%20also%20halted%20the%20supply%20of%20subsidised%20rice%20via%20FCI%20to%20ethanol%20distilleries%2C%20following%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fagri-business%2Fgovt-halts-supply-of-subsidised-rice-for-ethanol-assessing-impact-on-ebp%2Farticle67116321.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20they%20were%20diverting%20(re-selling)%20rice%20supplied%20by%20the%20FCI.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20initial%20ban%20on%20broken%20rice%20exports%2C%20ostensibly%20to%20direct%20supplies%20to%20the%20ethanol%20industry%20(via%20the%20FCI)%2C%20and%20its%20later%20decision%20to%20curb%20supplies%20from%20the%20FCI%20to%20the%20distilleries%2C%20thus%20appear%20paradoxical.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20happening%20in%20a%20scenario%20when%20state%20governments%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffci-rules-grain-food-fuel-karnataka%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebarred%20from%20buying%20rice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20Central%20Pool%20even%20at%20Rs%2031%20per%20kg%20for%20human%20consumption%2C%20particularly%20essential%20for%20Karnataka%20as%20it%20was%20seeking%20supplies%20for%20its%20food%20distribution.%20The%20distilleries%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20continue%20to%20receive%20FCI%20rice%20at%20Rs%2020%20per%20kg%2C%20which%20was%20incidentally%20reduced%20from%20the%20original%20Rs%2022%20per%20kg%20norm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20There%20are%20reports%20that%20the%20government%2C%20under%20pressure%20from%20ethanol%20producers%20who%20fear%20missing%20production%20targets%2C%20is%20considering%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fgovernment-considers-resuming-rice-supplies-for-ethanol-production-amid-shutdown-worries-over-production-targets-11691512399612.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eresumption%20of%20supplies%20of%20FCI%20rice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20distilleries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20ban%20on%20NBWR%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20July%2020%2C%20the%20government%20extended%20the%20export%20ban%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1941139%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENBWR%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20apparently%20in%20order%20to%20control%20domestic%20prices.%20Retail%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fmilk-and-rice-prices-remain-high-despite-falling-cpi-inflation-news-296180%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erice%20prices%20have%20increased%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%2011.5%25%20(from%20April-May%20last%20year)%20and%20by%203%25%20since%20June%20this%20year.%20But%20this%20price%20rise%20is%20for%20all%20varieties%20of%20rice%2C%20not%20just%20specific%20to%20NBWR.%20A%2020%20percent%20export%20duty%20has%20already%20been%20levied%20on%20NBWR%20exports%20since%20September%202022.%20Despite%20the%20high%20export%20duty%2C%20the%20exports%20were%20increasing%20significantly%20(35%25%20higher%20than%20the%20previous%20year)%20as%20prices%20in%20international%20markets%20were%20high.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFollowing%20India%E2%80%99s%20rice%20ban%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbusiness-news%2Fuae-bans-rice-exports-and-re-exports-for-four-months-1241785.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUnited%20Arab%20Emirates%20(UAE)%20also%20banned%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20rice%20exports%20and%20re-exports%20for%20four%20months%20for%20all%20varieties.%20Re-exports%20matter%20more%20for%20countries%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa%20for%20whom%20the%20UAE%20is%20a%20transit%20point%20for%20rice%20imported%20from%20India.%20A%20week%20after%20the%20Indian%20ban%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rt.com%2Fbusiness%2F580505-russia-rice-export-ban%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%20also%20banned%20rice%20exports%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20till%20December%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E31%20in%20order%20to%20stabilise%20prices%20in%20its%20domestic%20market.%20This%20was%20after%20Russia%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Black%20Sea%20Grain%20deal%2C%20which%20has%20already%20affected%20the%20global%20wheat%20and%20maize%20supply%20chains%20and%20prices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20credibility%20as%20a%20major%20rice%20exporter%20is%20at%20stake%20wherein%20such%20sudden%20reactionary%20bans%20raise%20concerns%20about%20reliability.%20Rice%20export%20bans%20were%20also%20imposed%20during%20the%20financial%20crisis%20of%202007-08.%20Back%20then%20also%2C%20follow-up%20bans%20and%20restrictions%20by%20other%20countries%20especially%20Vietnam%2C%20Thailand%2C%20and%20Pakistan%20caused%20an%20inflationary%20spiral%2C%20which%20dampened%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adb.org%2Fpublications%2Fwhen-policy-responses-make-things-worse-the-case-of-export-restrictions-on-agricultural-products%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etrade%20volumes%20globally%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F19134307%2F2020_4img16_Apr_2020_PTI16-04-2020_000200B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F19134307%2F2020_4img16_Apr_2020_PTI16-04-2020_000200B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F19134307%2F2020_4img16_Apr_2020_PTI16-04-2020_000200B-300x197.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F19134307%2F2020_4img16_Apr_2020_PTI16-04-2020_000200B-1024x671.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-449638%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22786%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWorkers%20carry%20sacks%20of%20rice%20after%20unloading%20them%20from%20a%20wagon%20train%20at%20an%20FCI%20godown%20in%20Jammu%2C%20April%2016%2C%202020.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20implications%20for%20global%20rice%20trade%20and%20food%20security%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECountries%20in%20Sub-Saharan%20Africa%2C%20middle-east%20and%20North%20Africa%20are%20most%20exposed%20in%20terms%20of%20rice%20export%20price%20inflation%20due%20to%20the%20ban.%20More%20than%2040%20countries%20rely%20on%20India%20for%20more%20than%20half%20their%20rice%20imports%2C%20with%20some%20African%20and%20south%20Asian%20nations%20importing%20more%20than%2080%20percent%20of%20their%20rice%20from%20India.%20In%202021%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20share%20in%20their%20rice%20imports%20was%20%E2%80%93%20Benin%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foec.world%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fbilateral-product%2Frice%2Freporter%2Fben%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E65.4%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Senegal%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foec.world%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fbilateral-product%2Frice%2Freporter%2Fsen%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E70.4%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Togo%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foec.world%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fbilateral-product%2Frice%2Freporter%2Ftgo%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E88.69%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Nepal%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foec.world%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fbilateral-product%2Frice%2Freporter%2Fnpl%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E99.4%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Guinea%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foec.world%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fbilateral-product%2Frice%2Freporter%2Fgin%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E78.9%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20and%20Bangladesh%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foec.world%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fbilateral-product%2Frice%2Freporter%2Fbgd%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E92%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20Other%20major%20destinations%20of%20NBR%20exports%20are%20China%2C%20Cote%20D%E2%80%99Ivoire%2C%20Guinea%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20Kenya.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20rice-importing%20countries%20are%20worried%20and%20are%20exploring%20the%20possibilities%20of%20official%20bilateral%20contracts%20with%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fsingapore-in-close-contact-with-indian-authorities-to-seek-exemption-from-non-basmati-rice-export-ban-11049361.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESingapore%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20imports%2040%25%20of%20its%20rice%20from%20India%2C%20has%20already%20reached%20out%20to%20Indian%20authorities%20seeking%20an%20exemption%20from%20the%20ban.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fworld-news%2Fphilippines-must-import-rice-as-el-nino-looms-may-look-to-india-marcos%2Farticleshow%2F102230162.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPhilippines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fears%20spike%20in%20domestic%20rice%20prices%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20onset%20of%20El-Nino%2C%20and%20is%20exploring%20bilateral%20contracts%20with%20India%20as%20buyers%20in%20Vietnam%E2%80%99s%20markets%20(their%20primary%20source%20and%20third%20largest%20exporter%20globally)%20are%20increasing.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fagri-business%2Fdomestic-white-rice-prices-drop-by-4000tonne-after-export-ban%2Farticle67120396.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESenegal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20imposed%20stringent%20stock%20limits%20held%20by%20traders%20as%20Indian%20companies%20are%20reportedly%20hoarding%20rice%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20share%20in%20global%20NBR%20exports%2C%20both%20parboiled%20and%20white%2C%20was%2029.07%25%20in%202021.%20Other%20major%20exporters%20of%20NBR%20and%20their%20respective%20shares%20in%20world%20exports%20are%20Thailand%20(13%25)%2C%20Vietnam%20(12%25)%2C%20USA%20(8%25)%2C%20Pakistan%20(8%25)%2C%20China%20(4%25)%2C%20and%20Cambodia%20(3%25).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fao.org%2Fmarkets-and-trade%2Fcommodities%2Frice%2Ffao-rice-price-update%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erice%20prices%20are%20at%2012%20year%20high%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20with%20All%20Rice%20Price%20Index%20(of%20Food%20and%20Agricultural%20Organization%20of%20the%20United%20Nations)%20rising%20by%202.8%20percent%20in%20July%202023%2C%20and%20peaking%20at%20its%20highest%20nominal%20value%20since%20September%202011.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.thesaigontimes.vn%2Fvietnam-rice-prices-soar-sharply%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVietnam%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20Thailand%20stand%20to%20gain%20the%20most%2C%20having%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fagri-business%2Fafter-indias-ban-on-white-rice-exports-thailand-and-vietnam-hike-prices%2Farticle67106546.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehiked%20prices%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20rice%20exports.%20Pakistan%20might%20benefit%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20rice%20ban%20as%20it%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20prime%20exporters%20of%20rice%20of%20the%20same%20quality%20as%20India.%20Pakistani%20exports%20are%20likely%20to%20increase%20because%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.siasat.com%2Fdemand-for-rice-from-pakistan-goes-up-as-india-bans-export-2657894%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreased%20demand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20Mexico%20and%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20about%20the%20Indian%20farmers%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rice%20trade%20in%20India%20is%20dominated%20by%20private%20players%20because%20government%20procurement%20is%20confined%20to%20five%20rice%20producing%20states%20in%20India.%20Government%20procurement%20is%20above%20two-thirds%20of%20production%20in%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Telangana.%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%2C%20along%20with%20Western%20UP%2C%20account%20for%2097%25%20of%20the%20Basmati%20cultivation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETrade%20intermediaries%20as%20well%20as%20farmers%20of%20northwest%20India%20are%20less%20bothered%20with%20NBWR%20ban%20because%20their%20basmati%20rice%20is%20exported%20globally%20via%20private%20trade%20and%20most%20of%20NBR%20is%20procured%20by%20the%20government%20at%20minimum%20support%20prices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20rice%20cultivating%20parts%20of%20India%2C%20NBR%20of%20all%20varieties%20and%20kinds%20is%20predominant.%20After%20the%20NBWR%20export%20ban%2C%20the%20supply%20kept%20for%20export%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20redirected%20domestically%20and%20might%20lead%20to%20reduction%20in%20domestic%20prices%20of%20rice.%20Given%20the%20bigger%20role%20played%20by%20private%20trade%20in%20non-basmati%20growing%20states%20where%20government%20procurement%20is%20low%2C%20it%20appears%20unlikely%20that%20private%20trade%20would%20come%20under%20significant%20pressure%20to%20reduce%20their%20margins%20because%20of%20the%20export%20ban.%20Indeed%2C%20when%20prices%20were%20rising%20even%20before%20the%20ban%2C%20they%20were%20benefiting%20the%20most%3B%20and%2C%20farmers%20are%20unlikely%20to%20benefit%20meaningfully%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20public%20procurement.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20private%20exporters%20may%20lose%20their%20ability%20to%20profiteer%20from%20exports%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20higher%20domestic%20prices%20offers%20them%20some%20compensation.%20Indeed%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20that%20the%20squeeze%20on%20their%20margins%20may%20well%20be%20offset%20by%20farmers%20being%20shortchanged%20by%20offering%20them%20low%20prices%2C%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F2277976019851930%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etendency%20observed%20before%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDomestic%20rice%20availability%20concerns%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMonth-wise%20rice%20stocks%20in%20the%20Central%20Pool%20have%20always%20remained%20much%20above%20the%20buffer%20stock%20norm%20for%20all%20benchmark%20months%20(see%20Figure%201%20below).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19160332%2FScreenshot-2023-08-19-at-4.03.21-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19160332%2FScreenshot-2023-08-19-at-4.03.21-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19160332%2FScreenshot-2023-08-19-at-4.03.21-PM-300x194.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19160332%2FScreenshot-2023-08-19-at-4.03.21-PM-1024x663.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668729%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22481%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20incredibly%2C%20the%20stock-holding%20norm%20itself%20has%20not%20changed%20since%202015.%20That%20normative%20standard%20would%20appear%20to%20be%20outdated%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20pandemic%20and%20its%20aftermath.%20Rice%20stocks%20on%20July%201%20this%20year%20were%20roughly%2070%20LT%20less%20than%20the%20available%20stocks%20at%20the%20same%20period%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20question%20of%20possible%20shortage%20in%20the%20Central%20Pool%20hinges%20crucially%20on%20how%20much%20the%20government%20procures%20after%20the%20next%20kharif%20harvest.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20significant%20because%20the%20performance%20on%20the%20procurement%20front%20has%20not%20been%20encouraging%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20The%20ratio%20of%20procurement%20to%20production%20has%20been%20decreasing%20from%2048%25%20in%202020-21%20to%2044%25%20in%202021-22%20and%20was%20at%2042%25%20in%202022-23.%20This%20is%20despite%20rice%20production%20increasing%20from%201243.7%20LT%20to%201355.4%20LT%20in%20the%20same%20period.%20In%20fact%2C%20state%20procurement%20fell%20from%20602%20LMT%20in%202020-21%20to%20570%20LMT%20in%202022-23%2C%20a%20drop%20of%205%25%2C%20even%20as%20output%20increased%20by%209%25%20during%20this%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKnee-jerk%20reaction%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20current%20stocks%20of%20rice%20are%20with%20traders%2C%20millers%2C%20and%20exporters%3B%20these%20will%20be%20most%20affected%20by%20the%20export%20bans.%20These%20bans%20are%20unlikely%20to%20benefit%20farmers%20immediately%20or%20directly.%20Regionally%2C%20the%20ban%20will%20have%20a%20bigger%20impact%20on%20non-basmati%20rice%20cultivating%20regions%20(south%2C%20east%2C%20and%20central%20India)%20where%20private%20trade%20plays%20a%20more%20crucial%20role%20in%20procurement%2C%20which%20curtails%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20government%20to%20ensure%20adequate%20availability%20at%20a%20reasonable%20price%20through%20its%20distribution%20channels.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20bans%20are%20a%20result%20of%20worries%20that%20spiralling%20grain%20prices%20could%20turn%20into%20a%20major%20issue%20in%20the%20election%20cycle%20that%20looms.%20However%2C%20export%20bans%20are%20unlikely%20to%20result%20in%20dampening%20prices%2C%20primarily%20because%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20procure%20more%20through%20direct%20intervention%20in%20the%20market%20for%20agricultural%20produce.%20Export%20bans%20on%20grains%20are%20generally%20not%20the%20preferred%20policy%20tool%20because%20such%20exports%20have%20global%20implications%20for%20price%20stability%20and%20food%20security.%20From%20a%20national%20food%20security%20standpoint%2C%20the%20export%20ban%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20knee-jerk%20reaction%20to%20rising%20domestic%20prices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKunal%20Munjal%20is%20Senior%20Research%20Fellow%2C%20Economic%20Analysis%20Unit%2C%20Indian%20Statistical%20Institute%20(ISI)%2C%20Bengaluru%20and%20Ph.D.%20candidate%2C%20Dept.%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%2C%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(IIT)%2C%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692443720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19161235%2F31764443254_73b92a3ef0_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-the-rice-export-ban-by-india-has-achieved%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ban%20on%20rice%20exports%20has%20disrupted%20global%20markets%2C%20threatening%20food%20security%20in%20the%20poor%20countries%20of%20Africa%20and%20South%20Asia.%20It%20is%20unlikely%20that%20either%20Indian%20consumers%20or%20farmers%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20move.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-the-rice-export-ban-by-india-has-achieved%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20an%20incoming%20Harvard%20freshman.%20I'm%20nervous%20I%20won't%20fit%20in%20with%20the%20rich%20kids%20on%20campus%20as%20a%20financial-aid%20student.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22731%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22headshot%20of%20Ezekiel%20Wells%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64de9393b698ac0019dbcc65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22548%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEzekiel%20Wells%20is%20an%20incoming%20Harvard%20freshman.%3Cp%3ELucas%20Kult-Banout%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESince%20I%20don't%20have%20rich%20parents%20or%20many%20connections%2C%20I%20could%20not%20see%20myself%20going%20to%20Harvard.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20during%20the%20application%20process%2C%20I%20suddenly%20pictured%20myself%20there%2C%20so%20I%20applied.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20accepted%3B%20I'm%20excited%20but%20nervous%20I%20won't%20fit%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20rising%20senior%20in%20high%20school%2C%20I%20was%20in%20Boston%20last%20summer%20to%20visit%20MIT%2C%20Northeastern%2C%20and%20Boston%20University.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Harvard%20wasn't%20in%20the%20picture.%20It%20seemed%20like%20an%20elitist%20club%20meant%20for%20the%20ultrawealthy.%20As%20a%20middle-class%20student%20from%20Illinois%2C%20I%20thought%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpreferred-cheap-community-college-over-georgetown-2023-4%5C%22%3EHarvard%3C%2Fa%3E%20wasn't%20built%20for%20people%20like%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20walk%20by%20the%20Cambridge%20campus%2C%20which%20was%20crowded%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fa-day-in-the-life-senior-georgetown-university-college-2023-5%5C%22%3Estudents%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20tourists%2C%20but%20from%20my%20brief%20exposure%2C%20I%20remember%20reporting%20to%20my%20friends%20that%20it%20was%20uninteresting%20and%20underwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20apply%20anyway%2C%20and%20under%20a%20year%20later%2C%20I%20anxiously%20clicked%20on%20the%20decision%20letter.%20Confetti%20appeared%20on%20the%20screen.%20A%20video%20played%20at%20the%20bottom.%20%26quot%3BCongratulations!%20I%20am%20delighted%20to%20inform%20you%20that%20the%20Committee%20on%20Admissions%20has%20admitted%20you%20to%20the%20Harvard%20College%20Class%20of%202027.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20not%20have%20been%20more%20thrilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20initially%20believed%20that%20Harvard%20was%20stuck%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20when%20I%20spoke%20with%20my%20interviewer%20and%20learned%20about%20my%20financial-aid%20package%2C%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20the%20perfect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-college-academics-differ-between-us-uk-2023-4%5C%22%3Eschool%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20could%20not%20see%20myself%20as%20a%20Harvard%20student%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20be%20careful%2C%26quot%3B%20my%20dad%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20applied%20to%20name-brand%20schools%2C%20my%20parents%20worried%20about%20the%20exclusive%20nature%20of%20wealthy%20circles.%20They%20supported%20my%20decisions%2C%20but%20like%20many%2C%20they%20assumed%20that%20the%20slots%20would%20be%20filled%20with%20legacy%20students%2C%20recruited%20athletes%2C%20and%20people%20whose%20parents'%20names%20topped%20the%20donor%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20those%20top%20donors%2C%20my%20parents%20went%20between%20substitute%20teaching%20and%20freelance%20work.%20While%20they%20worked%20hard%20to%20support%20our%20household%2C%20they%20knew%20little%20about%20the%20application%20process%2C%20and%20we%20had%20no%20affiliation%20with%20Harvard%20University.%20They%20have%20always%20been%20incredibly%20supportive%20of%20my%20education%2C%20but%20I%20simply%20come%20from%20a%20different%20financial%20background%20and%20lived%20experience%20than%20the%20stereotypical%20Harvard%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feared%20that%20all%20their%20students%20would%20be%20rich%20and%20well%20connected%2C%20that%20they%20would%20be%20arrogant%20or%20weird%2C%20and%20that%20the%20environment%20would%20feel%20unwelcoming%20for%20an%20average%20kid%20who%20went%20to%20public%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20I%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20Harvard%20and%20its%20student%20body%20during%20the%20application%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20my%20fears%2C%20I%20was%20encouraged%20to%20apply%2C%20so%20I%20threw%20my%20hat%20in%20the%20regular%20decision%20pool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20surprise%20was%20the%20interview.%20When%20the%20alumnus%20asked%20whether%20I%20had%20any%20questions%20or%20concerns%2C%20I%20told%20her%20my%20worries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20assumed%20she%20came%20from%20money%2C%20but%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20she%20was%20a%20recent%20immigrant%20who%20was%20able%20to%20graduate%20because%20of%20Harvard's%20financial%20aid.%20As%20she%20detailed%20her%20own%20time%20at%20Harvard%2C%20I%20was%20intrigued.%20She%20spoke%20about%20a%20lunch%20chat%20she%20had%20with%20the%20dean%20of%20admissions%20on%20this%20issue.%20It%20sounded%20like%20the%20university%20was%20genuinely%20trying%20to%20increase%20economic%20diversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20learned%20more%2C%20I%20became%20more%20excited%20about%20the%20school.%20If%20I%20got%20in%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Harvard%20website%20and%20net-cost%20calculator%2C%20it%20would%20be%20not%20only%20affordable%20but%20also%20my%20cheapest%20option.%20I%20learned%20it%20was%20more%20likely%20than%20not%20that%20my%20financial-aid%20package%20would%20cover%20everything%2C%20including%20stipends%20for%20living%20expenses.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20could%20be%20a%20Harvard%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20I%20expected%20to%20happen%2C%20happened.%20I%20got%20into%20Harvard.%20My%20stellar%20financial%20package%20covered%20my%20tuition%20and%20expenses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20remain%20nervous%20but%20optimistic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20had%20mixed%20feelings%20about%20the%20student%20body.%20I%20questioned%20how%20I%2C%20as%20a%20student%20on%20full%20financial%20aid%2C%20could%20find%20my%20seat%20at%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20school%20that%20relies%20so%20heavily%20on%20a%20process%20where%20students%20apply%20and%20interview%20for%20extracurricular%20activities%2C%20I%20could%20not%20help%20but%20wonder%20how%20big%20a%20factor%20wealth%20and%20connections%20might%20play%20in%20the%20success%20of%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20headed%20to%20Harvard%20for%20a%20prospective-student%20weekend%20recently%20and%20met%20my%20future%20classmates.%20It%20helped%20ease%20my%20fears.%20My%20prospective%20classmates%20came%20from%20diverse%20financial%20and%20cultural%20backgrounds%2C%20and%20we%20were%20curious%20to%20learn%20about%20our%20shared%20and%20contrasting%20experiences.%20Wealthy%20students%20definitely%20do%20attend%20Harvard%2C%20but%20the%20undergraduate%20population%20seems%20to%20blend%20together%20in%20a%20way%20that%20I%20had%20not%20previously%20imagined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20most%20of%20my%20buddies%20from%20high%20school%2C%20I%20leave%20later%20this%20month.%20I%20could%20not%20be%20more%20excited%2C%20and%20I%20remain%20nervous%20but%20optimistic%20about%20the%20road%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20Harvard%20built%20for%20the%20top%201%25%2C%20or%20does%20it%20cultivate%20a%20space%20where%20everyone%20belongs%3F%20As%20I%20move%20on%20to%20the%20next%20phase%20of%20my%20life%2C%20only%20time%20will%20tell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fincoming-harvard-university-freshman-tuition-financial-aid-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692443581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64de939dbd98a600197899bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fincoming-harvard-university-freshman-tuition-financial-aid-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ezekiel%20Wells%20thought%20Harvard%20was%20only%20for%20rich%2C%20well-connected%20kids.%20But%20when%20he%20got%20a%20full%20financial-aid%20package%2C%20he%20enrolled%20in%20his%20dream%20school.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ezekiel%20Wells)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fincoming-harvard-university-freshman-tuition-financial-aid-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Devendra%20Fadnavis%20Became%20Intolerant%20Since..'%3A%20Team%20Uddhav%3B%20BJP%20Reacts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EShiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%20on%20Saturday%20alleged%20that%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%2C%20who%20was%20earlier%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20has%20become%20intolerant%20and%20arrogant%20ever%20since%20he%20was%20made%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Fadnavis%20was%20a%20tolerant%20person%20earlier%2C%20but%20his%20frustration%20after%20being%20made%20the%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister%20resulted%20in%20him%20becoming%20intolerant%20and%20arrogant%2C%20the%20party%20claimed%20in%20an%20editorial%20in%20its%20mouthpiece%20'Saamana'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20however%2C%20objected%20to%20the%20language%20used%20in%20the%20editorial%20piece%20in%20the%20Marathi%20daily%2C%20whose%20editor%20is%20Sena%20(UBT)%20chief%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%2C%20while%20the%20executive%20editor%20is%20party's%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20Sanjay%20Raut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%20BJP%20chief%20Chandrashekhar%20Bawankule%20said%20one%20should%20maintain%20decorum%20while%20criticising%20political%20opponents.%20He%20also%20warned%20of%20filing%20a%20complaint%20against%20'Saamana'%2C%20and%20said%20its%20%26quot%3Bvitriol%26quot%3B%20needs%20to%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Fadnavis%20was%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20the%20state%20between%202014%20and%202019%20when%20the%20BJP%20and%20Shiv%20Sena%20(undivided)%20shared%20power.%20After%20the%202019%20assembly%20elections%20the%20two%20parties%20parted%20ways%20over%20sharing%20the%20Chief%20Minister's%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Thackeray%20later%20joined%20hands%20with%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20and%20the%20Congress%20to%20form%20the%20Maha%20Vikas%20Aghadi%20(MVA)%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Thackeray-led%20dispensation%2C%20however%2C%20collapsed%20in%20June%202022%20after%20his%20senior%20party%20leader%20Eknath%20Shinde%20rebelled%20along%20with%2039%20other%20MLAs%20and%20joined%20hands%20with%20the%20BJP.%20Mr%20Shinde%20became%20the%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20while%20Mr%20Fadnavis%20was%20made%20his%20deputy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20senior%20NCP%20leader%20Ajit%20Pawar%20and%20his%20party%20MLAs%20also%20joined%20the%20Shinde%20government%20with%20Mr%20Pawar%20being%20made%20the%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BDevendra%20Fadnavis%20would%20have%20returned%20to%20power%20(post-2019%20assembly%20elections)%20had%20he%20not%20betrayed%20the%20Shiv%20Sena.%20However%2C%20his%20party's%20top%20leaders%20in%20Delhi%20sidelined%20him%20and%20made%20him%20deputy%20chief%20minister.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFadnavis%20was%20a%20tolerant%20person%20earlier%2C%20but%20his%20frustration%20after%20being%20made%20the%20deputy%20Chief%20Minister%20resulted%20in%20him%20becoming%20intolerant%20and%20arrogant...They%20made%20him%20share%20the%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister's%20post%20with%20Ajit%20Pawar%2C%20adding%20to%20his%20woes%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20Fadnavis%20who%20once%20said%20that%20he%20would%20send%20Ajit%20Pawar%20to%20jail%20and%20ensure%20that%20he%20would%20get%20rigorous%20imprisonment.%20But%20what%20is%20Fadnavis%20doing%20exactly%20now%20by%20sharing%20power%20with%20the%20same%20Ajit%20Pawar%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20party%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20those%20having%20serious%20corruption%20charges%20and%20facing%20allegations%20of%20assault%20against%20women%20are%20now%20the%20colleagues%20of%20Mr%20Fadnavis%2C%20it%20said%20adding%20that%20he%20should%20take%20care%20of%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bawankule%20hit%20out%20at%20Sena%20(UBT)%20over%20the%20editorial%20targeting%20Mr%20Fadnavis.%20He%20hit%20out%20at%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20was%20out%20of%20his%20senses%20after%20losing%20party%20and%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20reporters%20today%20in%20Nagpur%2C%20Mr%20Bawankule%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhenever%20Shiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%20chief%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20wants%20to%20criticise%20someone%2C%20he%20either%20uses%20the%20'Saamana'%20daily%20or%20asks%20Sanjay%20Raut%20to%20make%20a%20statement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Thackeray%20is%20frustrated%20and%20bewildered%2C%20he%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20even%20lost%20his%20party%20symbol.%20He%20is%20pained%20because%20he%20cannot%20return%20to%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bawankule%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NCP%20has%20joined%20hands%20with%20the%20BJP%20and%20Mr%20Thackeray%20has%20now%20realised%20that%20he%20made%20a%20mistake%20by%20backstabbing%20Mr%20Fadnavis%20in%202019%2C%20he%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObjecting%20to%20the%20language%20of%20the%20'Saamana'%20editorial%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20has%20to%20be%20a%20limit%20while%20criticising%20political%20opponents%20by%20a%20newspaper.%20Our%20leaders%20will%20soon%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20this...There%20could%20be%20some%20protest-like%20situation%20in%20Mumbai.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20take%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20rights%20of%20this%20newspaper%20and%20how%20they%20are%20using%20it%20(against%20us).%20We%20will%20file%20a%20complaint%20against%20'Saamana'.%20The%20kind%20of%20vitriol%20being%20spread%20by%20'Saamana'%20needs%20to%20stop.%20We%20will%20make%20out%20stand%20clear%2C%26q