held%20a%20secret%20communion%20service%20on%20the%20moon%20and%20consumed%20wine%20and%20bread.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENASA%20and%20other%20space%20agencies%20have%20banned%20alcohol%20in%20space%20because%20it%20can%20damage%20equipment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20astronauts%20have%20found%20ways%20around%20this%20and%20smuggled%20alcohol%20onto%20spacecrafts%20for%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussian%20cosmonauts%20have%20even%20hidden%20bottles%20of%20alcohol%20in%20their%20spacesuits%20and%20hollowed-out%20books.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESpace%20agencies%20have%2C%20understandably%2C%20banned%20the%20consumption%20of%20alcohol%20in%20space%2C%20but%20astronauts%20have%20been%20finding%20ways%20around%20this%20for%20decades%20by%20smuggling%20booze%20onto%20spacecrafts%20and%20getting%20drunk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ffuture%2Farticle%2F20170217-why-astronauts-are-banned-from-getting-drunk-in-space%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20specifically%20prohibits%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20any%20product%20that%20contains%20it%20like%20mouthwash%2C%20perfume%2C%20or%20aftershave%20because%20it%20contains%20chemicals%20like%20ethanol%20that%20can%20damage%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUse%20of%20alcohol%20and%20other%20volatile%20compounds%20are%20controlled%20on%20ISS%20due%20to%20impacts%20their%20compounds%20can%20have%20on%20the%20station's%20water%20recovery%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20G%20Huot%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20NASA's%20Johnson%20Space%20Center%20told%20BBC%20Future%20in%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20alcohol%20actually%20made%20it%20into%20space%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2Fbelief%2F2012%2Fsep%2F13%2Fbuzz-aldrin-communion-moon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20first%20moon%20landing%20in%201969%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Buzz%20Aldrin%20administered%20a%20secret%20communion%20service%2C%20The%20Guardian%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAldrin%20had%20brought%20along%20a%20plastic%20container%20of%20wine%20and%20some%20bread%20from%20Webster%20Presbyterian%20Church%20near%20Houston%20where%20he%20was%20an%20elder.%20He%20consumed%20both.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAldrin%20described%20the%20ceremony%20in%20a%201970%20copy%20of%20Guideposts%20magazine%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20poured%20the%20wine%20into%20the%20chalice%20our%20church%20had%20given%20me.%20In%20the%20one-sixth%20gravity%20of%20the%20moon%20the%20wine%20curled%20slowly%20and%20gracefully%20up%20the%20side%20of%20the%20cup.%20It%20was%20interesting%20to%20think%20that%20the%20very%20first%20liquid%20ever%20poured%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20and%20the%20first%20food%20eaten%20there%2C%20were%20communion%20elements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAldrin%20had%20intended%20to%20share%20the%20event%20publicly%20over%20the%20radio%2C%20but%20NASA%20kept%20it%20hushed%20up%20because%20it%20was%20tackling%20a%20lawsuit%20from%20an%20atheist%20Madalyn%20Murray%20O'Hair%20who%20was%20trying%20to%20prevent%20the%20practicing%20of%20religion%20on%20earth%2C%20in%20space%2C%20and%20even%20in%20or%20around%20the%20moon%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Guardian.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20then%20officially%20clamped%20down%20on%20booze%20in%20space%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supercluster.com%2Feditorial%2Fwe-were-promised-cosmic-cocktails%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%201972%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20there%20have%20been%20at%20least%20two%20incidents%20where%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Fworld%2Famericas%2F6918801.stm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eastronauts%20were%20cleared%20to%20fly%20with%20booze%20in%20their%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20consuming%20alcohol%2012%20hou