ckpocket-yatra-youth-who-tracked-politicians-run-out-of-luck%2Farticleshow%2F102848230.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mission%20%E2%80%98ghar%20wapsi%E2%80%99%20to%20lure%20leaders%20to%20rejoin%20BRS%20ranks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692413049000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102848852%2Cimgsize-1058018.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fmission-ghar-wapsi-to-lure-leaders-to-rejoin-brs-ranks%2Farticleshow%2F102847552.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20it%20gives%20finishing%20touches%20to%20the%20first%20list%20of%20BRS%20candidates%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20released%20next%20week%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20is%20on%20a%20mission%20mode%20to%20counter%20the%20Congress%20by%20luring%20top%20leaders%20from%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20and%20also%20bringing%20back%20those%20who%20quit%20the%20party%20and%20joined%20Congress%20and%20BJP%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22KORIDE%20MAHESH%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fmission-ghar-wapsi-to-lure-leaders-to-rejoin-brs-ranks%2Farticleshow%2F102847552.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commissioners'%20Appointment%20Bill%3A%20Farewell%20to%20Free%20and%20Fair%20Elections%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2FElection_Commission_P1TI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20several%20state%20assembly%20elections%20and%20the%20parliament%20election%20coming%20up%20in%20the%20next%20one%20year%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20seems%20to%20be%20set%20on%20a%20%E2%80%98reform%E2%80%99%20mode.%20On%20August%2010%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20surreptitiously%20introduced%20the%20%E2%80%98Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20The%20objective%20is%20to%20replace%20the%20present%20arbitrary%20system%20of%20appointment%20of%20election%20commissioners%2C%20which%20is%20based%20on%20the%20executive%20considering%20a%20panel%20of%20candidates%20and%20selecting%20one%20considered%20acceptable%20from%20its%20point%20of%20view%20for%20approval%20by%20the%20President%20through%20a%20collegium%20method.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%207%20of%20this%20new%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20set%20up%20a%20selection%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20which%20will%20have%20one%20Union%20minister%2C%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20(LoP)%20as%20its%20members.%20Neither%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20nor%20any%20eminent%20jurist%20will%20find%20a%20place%20in%20this%20committee.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20other%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs)%20would%20be%20selected%20by%20the%20political%20executive%20belonging%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20with%20the%20LoP%20either%20ignored%20or%20overruled.%20What%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%9Cneutrality%20and%20independence%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20expected%20from%20such%20appointees%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20if%20providing%20a%20fig%20leaf%20to%20this%20predatory%20process%2C%20Section%206%20of%20the%20Bill%20constitutes%20a%20search%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20Cabinet%20secretary%20with%20two%20other%20secretaries%20as%20its%20members.%20This%20committee%20would%20consider%20candidates%20eligible%20to%20be%20appointed%20as%20ECs%20who%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20persons%20of%20integrity%2C%20who%20have%20knowledge%20of%20and%20experience%20in%20management%20and%20conduct%20of%20elections%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20recommend%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20such%20candidates%20for%20the%20selection%20committee%E2%80%99s%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Umpire%20Cannot%20be%20Subordinate%20to%20Team%20Captain%E2%80%99%3A%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20Raises%20Questions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20same%20Bill%20removes%20even%20this%20fig%20leaf%20with%20Section%208(1)%20laying%20down%20that%20the%20selection%20committee%20can%20regulate%20its%20own%20procedure%20for%20selecting%20the%20CEC%20or%20other%20ECs.%20What%20is%20worse%20is%20that%20Section%208(2)%20authorises%20this%20committee%20to%20consider%20any%20other%20person%20than%20those%20included%20in%20the%20panel%20by%20the%20search%20committee.%20This%20means%20the%20selection%20committee%20can%20go%20beyond%20the%20search%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20and%20appoint%20anyone%20it%20wants%20as%20CEC%2FEC%20thus%20reducing%20the%20entire%20%E2%80%98search%E2%80%99%20process%20to%20a%20farce%20and%20making%20it%20%E2%80%98functus%20officio%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20very%20start.%20In%20the%20event%2C%20sooner%20than%20later%20the%20CEC%2FECs%20could%20become%20products%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98spoils%20system%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20may%20become%20a%20den%20for%20political%20practitioners%20aligned%20to%20the%20ruling%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProbably%20in%20preparation%20thereof%2C%20Section%2010%20of%20the%20Bill%20downgrades%20the%20CEC%20and%20EC%E2%80%99s%20status%20to%20that%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20secretary%20from%20the%20level%20of%20the%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20as%20being%20treated%20now%20under%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20constitution.%20Could%20this%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20the%20ECI%20to%20become%20an%20executive%20authority%20instead%20of%20a%20constitutional%20body%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20not%20happen%20as%20long%20as%20the%20salutary%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20a%20fixed%20term%20for%20each%20EC%20%5BSection%209(1)%5D%2C%20prohibition%20of%20an%20EC%20being%20reappointed%20%5BSection%209(2)%5D%2C%20and%20a%20rigorous%20provision%20for%20the%20removal%20of%C2%A0%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20except%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20provisions%20contained%20in%20the%20first%20and%20second%20provisos%20of%20clause%20(5)%20of%20article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution%20%5BSection%2011%20(2)%5D%20are%20in%20place.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20with%20the%20downgrading%20of%20the%20posts%20of%20CEC%20and%20EC%2C%20these%20provisions%20can%20become%20increasingly%20tenuous%20and%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20status%20would%20subsist%20only%20by%20a%20slim%20thread.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fread-salient-sections-from-scs-judgment-on-appointments-to-election-commission%5C%22%3ERead%3A%20Salient%20Sections%20From%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Judgment%20on%20Appointments%20to%20Election%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20with%20this%20triple%20whammy%20is%20in%20response%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdecoding-the-supreme-courts-election-commission-judgment%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20WP(Civil)%20NO.104%20OF%202015%2C%20pronounced%20on%20March%202.%20While%C2%A0directing%20the%20government%20to%20consider%20introducing%20a%20more%20transparent%20system%20of%20appointment%20of%20the%20election%20commissioners%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20declare%20that%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20be%20made%20on%20the%20recommendations%20made%20by%20a%20three-member%20Committee%20comprising%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20in%20case%20no%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20is%20available%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20largest%20opposition%20party%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20terms%20of%20numerical%20strength%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKeeping%20in%20view%20the%20importance%20of%20maintaining%20the%20neutrality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20hold%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20which%20is%20a%20sine%20qua%20non%20for%20upholding%20the%20democracy%20as%20enshrined%20in%20our%20Constitution%2C%20it%20becomes%20imperative%20to%20shield%20the%20appointment%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20to%20be%20insulated%20from%20the%20executive%20interference%E2%80%A6.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20desirable%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20removal%20of%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20be%20the%20same%20as%20that%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20that%20is%20on%20the%20like%20grounds%20as%20a%20Judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20subject%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98recommendation%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%E2%80%99%20as%20provided%20under%20the%20second%20proviso%20to%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20not%20be%20varied%20to%20his%20disadvantage%20after%20appointment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20ensuring%20the%20%E2%80%9Cneutrality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20hold%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20do%20the%20very%20opposite%20by%20making%20it%20subservient%20to%20the%20whim%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20the%20day%2C%20thereby%20endangering%20the%20very%20purpose%20for%20which%20the%20commission%20is%20being%20constituted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERepugnant%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20an%20independent%20election%20commission%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBringing%20the%20ECI%20under%20the%20control%20of%20the%20political%20executive%20is%20repugnant%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20an%20independent%20election%20commission%20expounded%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20committee%20appointed%20to%20deal%20with%20fundamental%20rights%20wanted%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20elections%20and%20the%20avoidance%20of%20any%20interference%20by%20the%20executive%20in%20the%20elections%20to%20the%20legislature%20to%20be%20regarded%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20and%20provided%20for%20in%20the%20chapter%20dealing%20with%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F11193837%2Ftezpur-ec.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F11193837%2Ftezpur-ec.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F11193837%2Ftezpur-ec-300x145.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F11193837%2Ftezpur-ec-1024x496.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-354949%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEVM%20machines%2C%20VVPATs%20and%20other%20election%20material%20being%20distributed%20among%20polling%20officers%20ahead%20of%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20polling%20in%20Tezpur%2C%20April%2010%2C%202019.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FFile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20House%20affirmed%20without%20any%20kind%20of%20dissent%20that%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20purity%20and%20freedom%20of%20elections%20to%20the%20legislative%20bodies%2C%20it%20was%20of%20the%20utmost%20importance%20that%20they%20should%20be%20freed%20from%20any%20kind%20of%20interference%20from%20the%20executive%20of%20the%20day.%20Since%20the%20House%20wanted%20it%20to%20be%20provided%20for%20in%20some%20other%20part%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20drafting%20committee%20removed%20this%20question%20from%20the%20category%20of%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20put%20it%20in%20a%20separate%20part%20containing%20Articles%20289%2C%20290%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Article%20289%20did%20was%20to%20carry%20out%20that%20part%20of%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20by%20transferring%20the%20superintendence%2C%20direction%2C%20and%20control%20of%20the%20preparation%20of%20the%20electoral%20rolls%20and%20of%20all%20elections%20to%20parliament%20and%20the%20legislatures%20of%20states%20to%20a%20body%20outside%20the%20executive%20to%20be%20called%20the%20election%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20intent%20underlying%20the%20provisions%20in%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20as%20later%20approved%20by%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20(Article%20324%2C%20etc.)%20%E2%80%93%20was%20thus%20based%20on%20the%20fundamental%20premise%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%2C%20as%20any%20element%20of%20influence%20by%20the%20executive%20would%20result%20in%20an%20authority%20that%20would%20fail%20to%20inspire%20sufficient%20confidence%20among%20the%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20public%20in%20the%20impartiality%20of%20the%20commission%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReforming%20the%20mode%20of%20appointing%20election%20commissioners%20to%20ensure%20the%20%E2%80%9Cneutrality%20and%20independence%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20ECI%20has%20been%20a%20long-standing%20demand.%20But%20the%20Bill%20that%20has%20been%20introduced%20is%20a%20mockery%20of%20this%20demand.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Madan%20B.%20Lokur%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20spirit%20of%20the%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20quite%20clear%20that%20the%20election%20machinery%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20an%20irony%20that%20the%20present%20government%E2%80%99s%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%98reform%E2%80%99%20is%20to%20defy%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20decision%20and%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20ECI%20appears%20to%20be%20more%20beholden%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20(PMO)%20than%20the%20people%20of%20India%2C%20thereby%20raising%20doubts%20about%20the%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20process.%20This%20Bill%20will%20make%20things%20worse%20by%20making%20the%20ECI%20virtually%20subservient%20to%20the%20PMO.%20In%20which%20case%2C%20we%20might%20as%20well%20bid%20farewell%20to%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cworld%E2%80%99s%20largest%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fm-g-devasahayam-2%5C%22%3EM.G.%20Devasahayam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20Army%20and%20IAS%20officer%20and%20coordinator%20of%20the%20Citizen%E2%80%99s%20Commission%20on%20Elections.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692408659000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2FElection_Commission_P1TI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%22%2C%22summary