lways)%20Railways%20Finances%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20revealed%20that%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20could%20not%20generate%20a%20net%20surplus%20during%202021-22%20as%20compared%20to%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Operating%20Ratio%20(OR)%20was%20107.39%25%20in%202021-22%20against%2097.45%25%20in%202020-21.%C2%A0Operating%20Ratio%20refers%20to%20the%20ratio%20of%20working%20expenses%20to%20gross%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20higher%20ratio%20indicates%20a%20poorer%20ability%20to%20generate%20surplus.%20Against%20the%20target%20of%2096.15%25%20in%20the%20Budget%20Estimates%2C%20the%20OR%20of%20Railways%20was%20107.39%25%20in%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20meant%20that%20railways%20spent%20Rs%20107.39%20to%20earn%20Rs%20100.%20As%20compared%20to%20the%20Operating%20Ratio%20of%2097.45%25%20during%202020-21%2C%20there%20was%20deterioration%20in%202021-22%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20compared%20to%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20OR%20was%20the%20highest%20in%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017-19%20the%20OR%20was%2098.44%25%2C%20followed%20by%2097.29%25%20in%202018-19%2C%2098.36%25%20in%202019-20%2C%2097.45%25%20in%202020-21%20and%20107.39%25%20in%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C..the%20OR%20of%20Indian%20Railways%20reached%20an%20all-time%20high%20of%20107.39%25%20in%202021-22%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said%20citing%20the%20five-year%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20the%20Gross%20Traffic%20Receipts%20increased%20by%2036.02%25%20during%202021-22%20as%20compared%20to%202020-21%20due%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20passenger%20earnings%2C%20other%20coaching%20earnings%2C%20and%20freight%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20total%20expenditure%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Railways%20(MoR)%2C%20%E2%80%9Cincreased%20by%2035.19%25%2C%20the%20capital%20expenditure%20increased%20by%2022.61%25%20during%202021-22%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20revenue%20expenditure%20increased%20by%2049.30%25%20during%20the%20year.%20MoR%20incurred%20around%2075.83%25%20of%20the%20total%20working%20expenses%20on%20staff%20cost%2C%20pension%20payments%2C%20and%20lease%20hire%20charges%20on%20rolling%20stock.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20found%20that%20the%20Railways%20incurred%20an%20additional%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%207%2C778.43%20crore%20more%20than%20the%20sanctioned%20budget%20of%20Rs%205%2C7626.20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreatment%20for%20the%20dead%20and%20discharge%20before%20surgery%20under%20Ayushman%20Bharat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119060%5C%22%3Ereport%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20the%20Performance%20Audit%20of%20Ayushman%20Bharat-Pradhan%20Mantri%20Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%20%E2%80%93%20Union%20Government%20(Civil)%20National%20Health%20Authority%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare%20%E2%80%93%20has%20found%20several%20instances%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fayushman-bharat-cag-report-pmjay-corruption%5C%22%3E%20corruption%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20schemes%20on%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20audit%20included%20the%20time%20period%20of%20September%202018%20to%20March%202021.%C2%A0The%20audit%20was%20conducted%20on%20964%20hospitals%20in%20161%20districts%20of%20all%2028%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20(UTs).%20Delhi%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal%20have%20opted%20out%20of%20this%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20auditors%20found%20large-scale%20corruption%20in%20insurance%20claims%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202.25%20lakh%20cases%2C%20the%20date%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98surgery%E2%80%99%20done%20was%20shown%20to%20be%20later%20than%20the%20date%20of%20discharge.%20More%20than%201.79%20lakh%20such%20cases%20were%20found%20in%20Maharashtra%20for%20which%20the%20claimed%20amount%20was%20over%20Rs%20300%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20instances%2C%20the%20hospitals%20had%20made%20claims%20and%20the%20State%20Health%20Authority%20(SHA)%20transferred%20money%20for%20dates%20even%20before%20the%20inception%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELakhs%20of%20claims%20continued%20to%20be%20made%20against%20some%20who%20had%20been%20shown%20as%20%E2%80%98deceased%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20database.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20stipulates%20that%20a%20unique%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%20(PMJAY)%20ID%20should%20be%20issued%20to%20beneficiaries%20once%20verification%20is%20complete.%20The%20audit%20discovered%20that%201.57%20lakh%20unique%20IDs%20appeared%20more%20than%20once%20in%20the%20database.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20widespread%20reporting%20on%20the%20CAG%20report%20including%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20health%20ministry%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2017%2C%20issued%20a%20press%20release%20fact-checking%20media%20reporting%20on%20the%20CAG%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20was%20titled%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98Myths%20Vs%20Facts%3A%20Media%20Reports%20claiming%20AB%20PM-JAY%20beneficiaries%20who%20have%20been%20declared%20dead%20on%20the%20system%20availing%20treatment%20at%20hospitals%20are%20misleading%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-ministry-obfuscates-cag-findings-on-ayushman-bharat-to-train-guns-at-media-reports%5C%22%3Efour-page%20release%2C%20the%20ministry%20did%20not%20cite%20a%20single%20specific%20example%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewhere%20the%20media%20reports%20had%20been%20wrong%20in%20quoting%20the%20CAG%20report%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20to%20say%20the%20CAG%20report%20was%20misquoted%20or%20quoted%20out%20of%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPension%20scheme%20funds%20diverted%20to%20publicise%20other%20schemes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119044%5C%22%3Ereport%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20the%20Performance%20Audit%20of%20the%20National%20Social%20Assistance%20Programme%20%E2%80%93%20Union%20Government%20(Civil)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development%2C%20has%20found%20that%20funds%20meant%20to%20publicise%20the%20scheme%20were%20diverted%20for%20publicity%20of%20other%20schemes%20by%20the%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Social%20Assistance%20Programme%20(NSAP)%20is%20meant%20to%20provide%20social%20assistance%20benefits%20to%20the%20below%20poverty%20line%20(BPL)%20households%20in%20the%20case%20of%20old%20age%2C%20disabled%2C%20widows%2C%20and%20the%20death%20of%20the%20primary%20breadwinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20audit%20covered%20the%20period%20between%202017-18%20to%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NSAP%20includes%20five%20sub-schemes%2C%20of%20which%2C%20three%20are%20pension%20schemes%2C%20including%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20National%20Old%20Age%20Pension%20Scheme%20(IGNOAPS)%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20National%20Widow%20Pension%20Scheme%20(IGNWPS)%2C%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi%20National%20Disability%20Pension%20Scheme%20(IGNDPS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20two%20sub-schemes%20are%20the%20National%20Family%20Benefit%20Scheme%20(NFBS)%20%E2%80%93%20a%20one-time%20assistance%20to%20the%20bereaved%20family%20in%20the%20event%20of%20the%20death%20of%20the%20breadwinner%2C%20and%20the%20Annapurna%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20food%20security%20to%20the%20eligible%20old%20age%20persons%20who%20have%20remained%20uncovered%20under%20IGNOAPS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20funds%20of%20Rs%202.83%20crore%20earmarked%20for%20IEC%20(Information%2C%20Education%2C%20and%20Communication)%20activities%20under%20NSAP%20were%20diverted%20for%20%E2%80%9Ccampaigning%20of%20other%20schemes%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20audit%20added%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20prescribed%20procedure%20for%20proactive%20identification%20of%20beneficiaries%20coupled%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20IEC%20activities%20resulted%20in%20delayed%2Fnon-coverage%20of%20eligible%20beneficiaries%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20NSAP%20and%20non-achievement%20of%20universal%20coverage%20of%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development%20in%20January%202017%20decided%20to%20campaign%20through%20hoardings%20in%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20for%20giving%20due%20publicity%20to%20all%20programmes%2Fschemes%20of%20the%20Ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAdministrative%20approval%20and%20financial%20sanction%20of%20Rs%2039.15%20lakh%20was%20taken%20(June%202017)%20for%20a%20publicity%20campaign%20through%20hoardings%20with%20a%20limit%20of%2010%20hoardings%20at%20each%20capital%20city%20of%20the%20state%20and%20UT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdministrative%20approval%20and%20expenditure%20sanction%20of%20Rs%202.44%20crore%20was%20taken%20(August%202017)%20for%20campaigning%20Gram%20Samriddhi%2C%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Pakhawada%20and%20publicity%20material%20of%20multiple%20schemes%20of%20the%20Ministry%20through%20five%20hoardings%20in%20each%20District%20for%2019%20States.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20work%20orders%20were%20issued%20in%20June%20and%20September%202017%20and%20publicity%20campaigns%20were%20to%20be%20undertaken%20in%20September%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20funds%20for%20the%20said%20campaign%20were%20stated%20to%20be%20available%20under%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Scheme%20and%20were%20approved%20by%20the%20competent%20authority%20to%20be%20incurred%20under%20the%20same%20head%3B%20however%2C%20audit%20observed%20that%20funds%20were%20actually%20incurred%20from%20social%20security%20welfare-NSAP%20schemes%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20advertisement%20of%20only%20PMAY-G%20(Pradhan%20Mantri%20Awaas%20Yojana-%20Gramin%20)%20and%20DDU-GKY(Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyaya%20Grameen%20Kaushalya%20Yojana)%20schemes%20were%20mentioned%20in%20the%20work%20order%20and%20no%20schemes%20of%20NSAP%20were%20included%20in%20the%20work%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20the%20campaigns%20were%20to%20be%20undertaken%20by%20DAVP(Directorate%20of%20Advertising%20%26amp%3B%20Visual%20Publicity)%20under%20intimation%20to%20the%20department%3B%20however%2C%20the%20payment%20to%20DAVP%20was%20made%20without%20confirmation%20of%20the%20execution%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHence%2C%20planned%20IEC%20activities%20under%20NSAP%20were%20not%20undertaken%20as%20envisaged%20and%20funds%20of%20Rs%202.83%20crore%20were%20diverted%20for%20campaigning%20in%20respect%20of%20other%20schemes%20of%20the%20Ministry.%20Hence%2C%20IEC%20activities%20intended%20to%20create%20awareness%20among%20potential%20beneficiaries%20of%20NSAP%20could%20not%20be%20taken%20up%20even%20though%20there%20was%20earmarking%20of%20funds%20for%20IEC%20activities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20while%20the%20scheme%20is%20meant%20to%20include%20universal%20coverage%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20it%20was%20being%20implemented%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdemand-driven%20mode%20where%20benefits%20were%20provided%20to%20only%20those%20beneficiaries%20who%20applied%20for%20pensions%2Fbenefits%20under%20NSAP%20themselves%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20%E2%80%9Cidling%20of%20funds%20of%20Rs%2018.78%20crore%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20while%20one%20of%20the%20key%20principles%20of%20NSAP%20is%20regular%20monthly%20disbursement%20of%20pension%2C%20in%20eight%20States%2FUTs%2C%20funds%20received%20under%20NSAP%20were%20lying%20idle%20either%20with%20the%20states%2FUnion%20territories%20concerned%20or%20with%20implementing%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20included%20Bihar%2C%20Sikkim%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Goa%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20Tripura.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20%E2%80%9CRs%2018.78%20crore%20were%20lying%20idle%20in%20eight%20States%20for%20a%20period%20ranging%20from%20one%20to%20five%20years%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reasons%20for%20idling%20of%20funds%20were%20such%20as%20the%20release%20of%20funds%20at%20the%20fag%20end%20of%20the%20financial%20year%2C%20non-revalidation%20of%20funds%20from%20administrative%20department%2C%20duplication%20and%20non-permissible%20age%20limit%20of%20the%20beneficiaries%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20this%20also%20shows%20lack%20of%20financial%20monitoring%20on%20part%20of%20the%20States%2FUTs%20which%20manifested%20in%20irregular%20payment%20of%20pension%20to%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplementation%20of%20module%20for%20daily%20updation%20of%20exchange%20rate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119043%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Union%20Government%20(Indirect%20Taxes%20%E2%80%93%20Customs)%20contains%20significant%20results%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Audit%20of%20the%20Indian%20Customs%20Electronic%20Data%20Interchange%20System%20(ICES%201.5).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20test%20audit%20was%20conducted%20during%20December%202020%20to%20May%202022%20covering%20the%20period%202015-16%20to%202019-20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Indirect%20Taxes%20and%20Customs%20(CBIC)%20determines%20the%20rate%20of%20exchange%20of%20conversion%20of%20major%20transactional%20foreign%20currencies%20generally%20after%20every%2014%20days%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%20and%20issues%20Notifications%20(Non-Tariff).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20these%20Exchange%20Rate%20Notifications%2C%20the%20Directory%20Officer%20after%20getting%20the%20approval%20of%20Directory%20Manager%20of%20the%20Directory%20Management%20Site%20makes%20changes%20in%20ICES.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CImplementation%20of%20a%20system%20which%20captures%20daily%20fluctuation%20in%20the%20exchange%20rate%20will%20minimise%20the%20undue%20benefit%20or%20loss%20to%20importers%20and%20exporters%20and%20correspondingly%20to%20the%20Department%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20the%20filing%20of%20custom%20duty%20refunds%20is%20being%20done%20manually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Audit%E2%80%99s%20opinion%2C%20the%20work%20flow%20related%20to%20capturing%20and%20processing%20of%20refund%20claims%20needs%20to%20be%20automated%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20the%20GSTN%20(Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20Network)%20System.%20Decision%20of%20refund%20taking%20into%20considerations%20various%20factors%20like%20post%20adjudication%2C%20post-Appeal%2C%20double%20duty%20refund%2C%20refund%20due%20to%20re-assessment%20of%20duty%20etc%20could%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20competent%20authority%20online%2C%20with%20work%20flow%20automation.%20This%20will%20lead%20to%20effective%20monitoring%20and%20increase%20transparency%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692373593000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18205724%2FUntitled-design-5.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-on-indian-railways-expenses-ayushman-bharat-graft-diversion-of-pension-scheme-funds%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20part%20three%20of%20this%20series%2C%20'The%20Wire'%20looks%20at%20four%20of%2012%20reports%20filed%20by%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20on%20finances%2C%20performance%2C%20and%20corruption%20in%20key%20departments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-on-indian-railways-expenses-ayushman-bharat-graft-diversion-of-pension-scheme-funds%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Why%20is%20Remission%20Being%20Applied%20Selectively%3F'%20SC%20Questions%20Gujarat%20Govt%20in%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F25125105%2FScreenshot-2022-08-25-at-12.50.55-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20hearing%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20early%20release%20of%20Bilkis%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20rapists%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20questioned%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20remit%20their%20life%20sentence%20and%20set%20aside%20recommendations%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convicts%20concerned%20are%2011%20men%20who%20gangraped%20a%20pregnant%2019-year-old%20Bano%20and%20killed%20her%20relatives%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20trial%20was%20transferred%20to%20a%20court%20in%20neighbouring%20Maharashtra%20state%2C%20the%2011%20men%20were%20sentenced%20to%20life%20in%20prison%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifteen%20years%20later%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20it%20was%20up%20to%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-bilkis-case-remissions-8094290%2F%5C%22%3Eto%20decide%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20to%20release%20the%20men%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20state%20government%20release%20them%20from%20prison%20after%20considering%20the%20remission%20policy%20that%20was%20in%20force%20at%20the%20time%20they%20committed%20their%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Thursday%20(August%2017)%20for%20the%20Gujarat%20government%2C%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20S.V.%20Raju%20argued%20that%20even%20those%20who%20committed%20heinous%20crimes%20such%20as%20the%20accused%20in%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20case%20have%20a%20right%20to%20rehabilitate%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20put%20the%20following%20questions%20to%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIs%20the%20purpose%20of%20remission%20punishment%3F%20Does%20committing%20a%20heinous%20crime%20debar%20a%20convict%20from%20getting%20its%20benefit%2C%20even%20if%20the%20convict%20has%20reformed%20themselves%2C%20has%20displayed%20remorse%20and%20wants%20to%20start%20a%20new%20life%20again%3F%20Should%20the%20past%20always%20be%20dangling%20above%20your%20head%3F%20Should%20these%20convicts%20be%20condemned%20for%20all%20times%20to%20come%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-bilkis-bano-reformation-remission-policy-being-selectively-applied-235468%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funderstanding-the-remission-policy-that-led-to-the-release-of-bilkis-banos-rapists%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20the%20Remission%20Policy%20That%20Led%20to%20the%20Release%20of%20Bilkis%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20Rapists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaju%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20men%20were%20not%20given%20the%20death%20penalty%20seemed%20to%20suggest%20that%20there%20was%20scope%20for%20their%20reformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20law%20does%20not%20say%20that%20every%20convict%20should%20be%20hanged%2C%20or%20even%20punished%20perpetually%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20law%20speaks%20about%20giving%20a%20chance%20to%20even%20the%20most%20hardened%20criminal%20to%20reform%20themselves%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20doubted%20this%20was%20the%20only%20reason%20why%20these%2011%20men%20were%20given%20a%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20far%20is%20this%20law%20being%20applied%20to%20inmates%20in%20jail%3F%20Why%20are%20our%20jails%20overcrowded%3F%20Particularly%20with%20undertrials%3F%20Why%20is%20the%20policy%20of%20remission%20being%20applied%20selectively%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asked%20Raju.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20raised%20this%20question%20again%20during%20another%20point%20in%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20how%20far%20is%20the%20remission%20policy%20being%20implemented%20in%20cases%20where%20convicts%20have%20completed%2014%20years%3F%20Is%20remission%20policy%20being%20implemented%20in%20all%20such%20cases%2C%20subject%20of%20course%20to%20their%20eligibility%3F%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20her%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaju%20agreed%20that%20all%20eligible%20convicts%20must%20be%20given%20the%20opportunity%20to%20rehabilitate%20themselves%2C%20but%20said%20he%20did%20not%20have%20the%20statistics%20to%20answer%20Justice%20Nagarathna%E2%80%99s%20question%20at%20that%20point%20in%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20facts%20of%20a%20case%2C%20I%20may%20be%20able%20to%20answer%20%E2%80%A6%20you%20will%20have%20to%20have%20the%20statistics.%20The%20state-wise%20statistics.%20The%20opportunity%20to%20reform%20should%20be%20given%20to%20every%20prisoner.%20Not%20only%20to%20a%20few%20prisoners%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20according%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2FAhmedabad_riots1-1024x692.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2FAhmedabad_riots1-1024x692.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2F