%20how%20they%20work%2C%20Rennis%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFirst%2C%20we%20form%20a%20small%20group%20of%20say%20five%20students.%20We%20let%20them%20sit%20in%20a%20circle%2C%20not%20rows%20so%20that%20there%20is%20no%20difference%20between%20a%20front%20and%20a%20back-bencher.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20make%20a%20few%20groups%20of%204-5%20students%20each.%20We%20then%20ask%20one%20group%20to%20design%20a%20smart%20village%20with%20the%20best%20sustainable%20technology%20possible%2C%20we%20ask%20another%20group%20to%20redesign%20a%20hospital.%20They%20observe%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%20current%20system%20and%20come%20up%20with%20a%20design%20which%20they%20draw%20on%20a%20chart.%20While%20doing%20that%2C%20they%20build%20design%20thinking%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20try%20to%20promote%20positive%20interaction%20among%20peers.%20It%20helps%20them%20to%20build%20critical%20awareness%20and%20negotiations%20among%20team%20members%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERennis%20and%20his%20team%20work%20with%20any%20school%20for%20about%20four%20years%2C%20but%20remain%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20school%20to%20trace%20the%20impact.%20For%20instance%2C%20his%20team%20worked%20in%20Banapuram%20village%20of%20Telangana%20in%202010.%20After%20five%20years%20of%20this%20intervention%2C%20he%20says%2C%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20children%20going%20to%20schools%20in%20the%20villages%20were%20enrolled%20in%20higher%20education%20in%20colleges.%20%E2%80%9CIn%202019%2C%20we%20did%20a%20study%20to%20check%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%20We%20found%20that%20all%20the%20girls%20were%20still%20in%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20teaching%20the%20students%20through%20interactive%20sessions%2C%20they%20work%20to%20create%20a%20pool%20of%20teachers%20who%20can%20think%20of%20innovative%20ways%20to%20teach%20children%20after%20they%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%